<DOC><DOCNO> AP880314-0158 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-14-88 1630EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--AirportStrike     03-14 0128</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Airport Strike,0131</SECOND><HEAD>Strike Causes Cancellations, Delays at Rome Airport</HEAD><DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ground workers at the city's main airport walked offtheir jobs Monday for the second straight day, forcing cancellationof half of Alitalia's flights and delaying foreign carriers.   About 600 Alitalia workers at Leonardo da Vinci airport,including baggage handlers and maintenance crew, decided to strikefor six hours.   They were angered over a tentative contract agreement reached bygovernment and union negotiators on Sunday.   Union leaders criticized Monday's walkout, the latest strike ina dispute that has plagued air travelers since the fall. Unlikethis walkout, most of the strikes have been called in advance togive travelers a chance to find other transportation.   Foreign carriers reported delays of about 30 minutes Monday.</TEXT></DOC>